You are given an integer array nums.

Return the smallest index i such that the sum of the digits of nums[i] is equal to i.

If no such index exists, return -1.


Solution

class Solution {
    public int smallestIndex(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int num = nums[i];   
            int sum = 0;

            while (num > 0) {
                int digit = num % 10;
                num /= 10;       
                sum += digit;    
            }

            if (i == sum) {
                return i;
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
}
